h3. Problem Definition
As a Confluence administrator, I would like to have embedded Crowd 2.8.4 with the latest versions of Confluence. There are some critical bugs that have been corrected in Crowd 2.8.4, however, Confluence and JIRA still use embedded Crowd 2.8.3 in the latest versions:

ex) Latest version of Confluence from source still shows embedded Crowd 2.8.3 in the pom.xml file

{noformat:title=Pom.xml for Confluence}
   <!-- Update https://extranet.atlassian.com/display/INTEGRATION/Crowd+and+EMBCWD+Version+Matrix too -->
        <crowd.version>2.8.3</crowd.version>
        <crowd.embedded.version>2.0.1</crowd.embedded.version>
{noformat}

h3. Suggested Solution
Use embedded Crowd 2.8.4 or later in new releases for Confluence and JIRA.

