h5. Summary
 Images on a page with size more that 300 px are downloaded as original when viewing a page. So for eg: I have an image of 5 MB rendered on a page , the original image file is downloaded .
 However, When an image with size less than 300 px is rendered on a page this image is further compressed as shown as thumbnail.
 This can be considered as a regression of https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-28189

h5. Steps to Reproduce
 # Add an image to page ,
 # You can resize the pixel to 301 in the view file macro.
 # Save the page . View the developer console and refresh the page.
 # You will observe that the original image is downloaded.
 
h5. Possible Solutions
1. The Thumbnail version of the image should be downloaded and an option should be available to set the {{THUMBNAIL_DEFAULT_WIDTH = 300}}
This property is hard coded in the below Class
{code:java}
public class ThumbnailInfo {
    // default thumbnail max height and max width
    public static final int THUMBNAIL_DEFAULT_WIDTH = 300;
{code}
2. Provide thumbnails for a range of image sizes.

